        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 3:13PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 313 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Covington, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Covington...
Clifton Forge...
Eagle Rock...
Oriskany...
Jordan Mines...
Iron Gate...
and Douthat State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
